messages.message:
@Balaram Yes, all places where you are using INPUT_IBOCR, you’ll need to use INPUT_IBOCR_RECORD.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1J1Y23uwHu3LGAXmQWhhS3gDnpeUBwn38a1cTWaKuqW4/edit# describes how to handle them.

Here is a change I made to one of Kerry’s UDF as an example:

https://dogfood.instabase.com/ib_solutions/solutions/fs/Instabase%20Drive/pre-built/us-markets/w2/samples_kerry/scripts/format_w2.py

The before portion of it is commented out.

Noe that we are not pushing IBDOC changes to instabase.com (http://instabase.com) with this release.  The push to instabase.com (http://instabase.com) will happen next release cycle.  We should be able to update the UDFs by then.  Please let me know if you need help with the rewrites.
